title: Tesla 's net loss attributable to common stockholders 2013 to 2019
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Loss in million U.S. dollars. In total the number of data points it has is 7.
In general Loss in million U.S. dollars has rose over the Year.
Loss in million U.S. dollars is rapidly increasing from 2013 to 2015, roughly constant from 2015 to 2016, roughly increasing from 2016 to 2017, and lastly roughly constant from 2017 to 2019.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2016 and 2017.
The highest Loss in million U.S. dollars, of value 1962.0 was reached at Year 2017
Minimum Loss in million U.S. dollars about 74.0 was reached at Year 2013
